GET http://api.hypertheory.com/status- Singletons - addSingleton The same instance of that service will be shared across all requests for the lifetime of that application. Singletons must be written to be "thread safe" - There is no issue with this if the object is READ ONLY after it is created.- Scoped - addScoped - For THIS particular request - Create a new one when there is a request, hold on to a reference to that, and if any OTHER code during that request needs one of these, reuse the same one. - At the end of the request, dispose of it. - And requests all run on the same (logical) thread of execution.- Transient - addTransient - EVERY time you create one of these, create a brand new one of these (NEVER reuse it)
